sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS monthly_donors_count
FROM donor_segmentation
WHERE segment_name = 'Monthly donors';

SELECT segment_name, COUNT(donor_id) AS total_donors
FROM donor_segmentation
GROUP BY segment_name;

external_knowledge:
; Top donors are those with the highest total donations in each campaign; 
; Donation rank is a measure of a donor's total donation amount relative to others in the same campaign;
; Completion rate is calculated as the ratio of completed donations to total donations;
; Engagement rating and successful engagements are measures of donor engagement quality.

sql:
SELECT donor_id, SUM(donation_amount) AS total_donations
FROM donor_history
GROUP BY donor_id;

SELECT c.campaign_name
FROM campaigns c
WHERE c.campaign_roi = (
  SELECT MAX(campaign_roi)
  FROM campaigns
);

SELECT segment_name
FROM donor_segmentation
WHERE donor_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- Average donation amount refers to the mean of all donations made to a campaign; 
- Engaged donors are those who have participated in at least one engagement; 
- Goal achievement percentage is calculated as (total donations / campaign goal) * 100.
